Get ready to Socialise, Network, Dance & party with us Sat. 17th October for our grand Autumn Party our last opportunity to enjoy the Heated gardens & perhaps a BBQ outside before the weather turns to cold. Located 100 feet above Kensington High Street, the Roof Gardens is as glamorous as it comes. SILVER PIANO BAR exclusively for us till 10pm with complimentary Cocktail reception.  
 
SPECIAL £1 OFF ALL TICKETS FOR THOSE ON OUR MAILING LIST &/OR FOR THOSE THAT LIKE OUR FAN PAGE ON FACEBOOK. * 
* MUST EMAIL BEFORE BOOKING FOR DISCOUNT. 
8pm - 10pm Pre-Club Socialising with WELCOME COCKTAIL for EACH guest, we have the SILVER PIANO BAR reserved exclusively & you will be introduced to one another.  
From 10pm BBQ Time: Fancy a late night snackthe BBQ will be on all night with a selection of food straight from the BBQ to choose from. 
  
 
10pm - 3am: Live Music, More Drinking, Socialising & Dancing all together inside... You are more than welcome to stay at the club till closing time at 3am at no extra cost. 
Spread the word, invite your friends and meet lots of new people in one of Londons' most unique nightlife experiences.  
Doors open at 8pm. Last entry with our tickets is by 9.30pm... NO exceptions!!!! 
We expect this event to be sold out. Early booking is highly recommended as ticket prices will increase in price. 
IMPORTANT NOTES: 
1. Ticket is valid for the no. of people listed in Ticket name, if no. is not present then ticket is valid for 1 person. 2. Tickets are valid for entry Pre-9:30pm ON 17th October 2015 ONLY. NO EXCEPTIONS!  
3. Ticket INCLUDES Welcome Cocktail for those arriving PRE-8:30pm (to be redeemed at the bar pre-9pm) + Pre-Club Socialising in SILVER BAR. 
4. Ticket holders can remain for the Club party with DJ till 3am. 
5. DRESS CODE applies i.e. "no effort, no entry" so get glammed up and leave the trainers at home. If you have any questions in relation to dress code BEFORE the event please either email or phone The Roof Gardens or Email youngprofessionalsinlondon@hotmail.co.uk  
6. Ticket is NOT refundable / transferable, issues with entry to The Roof Gardens MUST be communicated on the night of the event whilst still at the venue via email to: youngprofessionalsinlondon@hotmail.co.uk  
7. Guests purchasing group / twin tickets are recommended to arrive together. 
8. Ticket does not need to be printed but please bring a printout / display of ticket on mobile phone if is purchased after 730pm on the night of the event. 
9. Ticket prices may increase without warning & as the event date approaches the only way to gaurantee entry at a certain price is by purchasing a ticket. 
10. This event WILL sell out so it's highly unlikely any tickets will be sold at the door.

Monday, October 19th 6pm-9pm 
Join hundreds of Manhattan's most beautiful young professionals for a one evening only art and jazz event with a performance by the Stephane Wrembel Trio for a dynamic skyline event. Admission is complimentary.  21+ to attend. Kindly RSVP. Featured artists to be announced.  
Doors open at 6pm
Dress code: business / summer chic
Venue Address: Gansevoort Park Avenue, Penthouse 2, 420 Park Avenue South 
-Penthouse 2 incorporates both indoor lounge space and poolside terrace.  Rain or shine this will be a spectacular evening. 
About Stephane Wrembel:
 
“A REVELATION” –Rolling Stone Magazine"Intense and full of charisma." -The New York Times"One the greatest guitar players I've ever seen ...and I don't say that lightly." –Relix Magazine"[Wrembel embodies] a John Coltrane-ish search for a moment of musical nirvana..." -Variety"A truly astonishing talent…" –All About Jazz
Composer Stephane Wrembel hits the road this winter – bringing his jaw dropping talent, palpable musical rapport with His Band, and vivid and textured compositions to life on theater stages along the east coast and Midwest. 
Parisian born Wrembel – whose music embraces all styles and influence to create a truly signature sound – is being hailed as one of the world’s most dynamic and inspired players out there today. Wrembel is indeed a standout – not only for his undeniable skills but also for his unparalleled ability to create a unique and vivid listener experience.

TICKET INFORMATION 

Once you purchase, you will receive an order confirmation email including your PDF ticket from Eventbrite on behalf of Beyond The Valley Music Festival. 
IMPORTANT: If you do not see your order confirmation in your email inbox, make sure you check your junk/spam folder. If you still do not see your order confirmation click here to access the Eventbrite help centre. 
If you are having any other technical ticketing-related issues with your order, click here to contact Eventbrite. For general festival info click here to keep up to date through our Facebook page.
All sales are final. No refunds or exchanges. 
Event is rain, hail or shine.
Artists and schedule is subject to change.
**Only purchase BTV tickets from the official Beyond The Valley ticketing page (you're here!). If you purchase from another source, you risk purchasing a counterfeit or invalid ticket. Beyond The Valley is not responsible for tickets purchased from unofficial sources. 

 
 
 
FAQs 
  
For all questions relating to ticket purchases, please contact Eventbrite here 
  
  
I missed out on 3-day tickets, will I miss artists on the lineup? 
  
No. 2-day tickets will allow you to see every artist on our lineup! The first day (29th December) is our pre-party with local bands and DJs. All of the artists on our main lineup will perform on the 30th and 31st of December.  
Are tickets only available online? 
If you do not want to buy tickets online, some hard copy tickets are available through friends of Beyond The Valley.  
Does my name need to be on the ticket?  
Yes. To ensure the validity of the ticket, we require your name to be on your ticket. At the event, security will check to ensure your name on your ID matches the name on your ticket. Please note that names only need to be on tickets purchased online. If you purchase a hard copy ticket from a promoter, your name does not need to be on it.  
Can I change the name on my ticket?   
Yes. Name changes will be available through our website from September 1st. Please note that name changes will incur an admin fee.  
Is camping included in my ticket?  
Yes, free onsite camping is included in the ticket price. All camping add-ons such as Electric City will need to be purchased in addition to a festival ticket.  
Do I have to buy a car pass? 
No. Provided all guests in a vehicle have a valid festival ticket no car pass is needed.  
My friend has a ticket that looks different to mine, is that okay?  
Yes. Due to the various means of attaining a Beyond The Valley ticket, yours may look different to others. Please ensure it is barcoded and branded by Eventbrite and if in doubt purchase online through the Beyond The Valley website.  
If I have a different ticket to my friends, can I still camp with them? 
No, cars will be allocated to campsite areas according to the passes they have. Eg. Electric City Pass, Luxury Camping Pass or General Camping. Please ensure all cars in your convoy have the same pass - For Example if you have a general ticket with no add-ons and your friends have an Electric City pass, you will need to purchase an Electric City ticket to be able to camp with them.  
Is there a limit on how many tickets I can buy? 
No. The more the merrier! 
Wristbands at the event?  
You will be issued a wristband when you get your ticket scanned at the festival. There are no replacements for lost wristbands; the only way they can be removed is with scissors. Wristbands will not be replaced and cannot be transferred to friends.  
Replacing lost tickets? 
If you cannot find your online ticket that you purchased, contact Eventbrite here. If you have purchased a hard ticket through a promoter you must treat this ticket as if it were cash. there are no replacements on hard copy tickets.   
  
 
  
By purchasing this ticket you accept the terms and conditions, terms of entry and our privacy policy. 

Click here to read our terms and confitions and terms of entry.
Click here to read our privacy policy.

M.C. W.A.R. Promotions LLC Presents: 
 
 
 ATLANTA HIP HOP DAY 
SEPTEMBER 26TH - 27TH 
AT ROBERT WOODRUFF PARK 
91 PEACHTREE ST., ATLANTA, GA 30303 
The 5th Annual Atlanta Hip Hop Day Festival is a free festival that pays tribute to the four elements of Hip Hop and Atlanta's contribution to Hip Hop as a whole. The Festival is held downtown Atlanta at Robert Woodruff Park. The four sides of the park are dedicated to the four elements of Hip Hop displaying B-Boy & B-Girl exhibits, Emcee Battles, Turntablism and Graffiti artists.  Entertainment Includes: 
Special Guest Performances By:

description.text:
Physics is Fun!  
We invite you to the 2016 University of Minnesota's Physics Force Winter Shows. 
These free-of-cost performances will take place at the Northrop Auditorium on the University's campus January 11-15,2016. 
The shows dates and times   
Monday 1/11  10:00 am & 1:00pm  Tues 1/12  10:00 am &  1:00pm  Wed 1/13 10:00am & 1:00 pm  Th  1/14 10:00 am, 1:00pm & 7:00pm  Fri 1/15  10 am & 1:00pm 
Each show is 60-75 minutes long.  Although the shows are free, reservations are required. Please reserve on this site. Reserve as many tickets as you need, but please reserve only if you intend to come. Seats are in high demand. Please cancel your tickets, or notify us of a cancellation by November 15, 2015.   
The system has a 100 ticket per order maximum so if you need more than 100 tickets, you will need to create more than one order. The same teacher's name can be used for all reservations. Include adults, teachers, and chaperones in your order number.  
The morning and afternoon shows are allocated to elementary and middle school classes. The Thursday evening show is open to the general public. This show is also free-of-cost, but reservation on this site is required. 
Some funding is available to help public schools with bus support. If you would like to apply for this funding please follow the link http://www.physics.umn.edu/resources/forms/pfbusing.html. You must apply by November 1, 2015  and you will be notified as to the amount that can be provided for your school before November 15th, 2015. 
If you will need support for hearing impaired students please use the link http://www.physics.umn.edu/resources/forms/SLI.html 
To learn more about the physics force and the show please go to http://www.physics.umn.edu/outreach/pforce/ 
The Physics Force is supported by the School of Physics and Astronomy, the College of Science and Engineering, and the University of Minnesota's Materials Research Science and Engineering Center (MRSEC)

Tickets purchased for the Opening Night Preview benefit the IFPDA Foundation  and include a complimentary day pass.  
Visit printfair.com for programs and events. 
PROGRAM: SATURDAY 11:00 am A Conversation with Kiki Smith moderated by Wendy Weitman Sponsored by the Jordan Schnitzer Family Foundation, this program is free and open to the public.   
FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS What is the refund policy? Tickets are nonrefundable. 
What can/can't I bring to the event? Attendees may not bring works of art to the event. All bags larger than a laptop computer must be checked.  
Children under 12 are admitted free when accompanied by an adult.  Children at the Fair can play EYE Spy, an activity that helps them to learn to look at art. 
Is the venue equipped for assisted access? A sidewalk level entrance is available at 103 East 66th Street, located just off Park Avenue. Arrangements can be made prior to your arrival to the Fair by calling the Armory's main security desk at (212) 616-3950, ext. 1. 
What are the exhibitors offering? Exhibitors are art dealers from London to Los Angeles who will present nearly six centuries of printmaking from early woodcuts and traditional engravings, etchings and lithographs to innovative contemporary projects. The wide historical spectrum of artists' works on view includes Old Masters; Japanese prints; 19th and early 20th century American masters; European Impressionists and Modernists, as well as German Expressionists. Editions publishers exhibiting at the Fair will premiere new editions by contemporary artists, both prominent and emerging. 
Are prints at the Fair for sale? Yes, works exhibited by dealers at the Fair are available for purchase. Exhibiting dealers are all members of the IFPDA and buyers are therefore assured of each dealer's expertise and professionalism, and of the authenticity and condition of artwork available for purchase. While the Fair offers many affordable works from all periods, museum curators and the world's most important collectors will acquire rare works in the six-figure range. 
About the IFPDA  The International Fine Print Dealers Association is a nonprofit organization of art dealers, galleries, and publishers in the field of fine prints committed to the highest standards of quality, ethics, and connoisseurship, and to promoting a greater appreciation of fine prints among collectors and the public. For more information about the IFPDA please visit www.ifpda.org.

Members must first click on "Enter Member ID or Enter Promotional Code" then enter your FONZ Member Number to access discounted tickets.

Boo at the Zoo Friday, October 23 from 5:30pm to 8:30pm Saturday, October 24 from 5:30pm to 8:30pm Sunday, October 25 from 5:30pm to 8:30pm   
Join us for Washington DC's favorite not-so-spooky Halloween haunt, Boo at the Zoo. 
All guests will have the opportunity to trick or treat at more than 40 treat stations throughout the decorated zoo, view animal demonstrations and listen to keeper chats.  New this year will be an entertainment stage featuring a DJ spinning Halloween favorites, magicians and jugglers.  This frightfully fun evening is a treat for the whole family. 
Please note the following: 

This is a rain or shine event. 
All guests two and older are required to purchase a ticket.
Tickets are only valid on the date you purchased.  For example, we will not accept Friday tickets on Saturday night.

FAQs 
Can I see animals at the event? 
Yes, some of our animals may be sleeping, but most of our animal exhibits will be open including: Bird House, Elephant Community Center, Small Mammal House, Great Apes, Reptile Discovery Center, Think Tank, Great Cats and Kids' Farm.  Unfortunately, due to the time of day our pandas are already resting for the evening and the house will not be open. 
What age range is approproiate for this event? 
The best suggested age range for child attendees is 4-12. 
Who needs to purchase a ticket? 
All guests two years old and older, adults included, must purchase a ticket.  
What are my transport/parking options getting to the event? 
Driving?  You must pre-purchase a parking ticket for the night you plan to attend.  Only guests with a valid parking ticket for each night will be able to park on Zoo grounds.  Drivers, please note that ONLY the Connecticut Avenue gates will be open for vehicles. 
Walking?  Two pedestrian entrances will be open.  Guests can enter through the Connecticut Avenue gates at the top of the Zoo or at the Harvard Street Bridge at the bottom of the Zoo. 
Taking Metro?  You can catch a ride from the Woodley Park Metro Station (red line) on a double decker shuttle bus provided by Big Bus Tours.  The shuttle will run continual loops throughout the night from the metro to the Bus Lot. 
Is my registration/ticket transferrable? 
The ticket you purchased is only valid on the night that you purchased it for.  For example, we will not accept Friday tickets on Saturday night.  
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event? 
You must bring either your printed ticket or the electronic version of your ticket to the event.

description.text:
HGM Shopping Hours:  
Friday, November 13th, 9:00am- 6:00pm Saturday, November 14th, 9:00am- 6:00pm Sunday, November 15th 9:00am – 5:00pm 
Please join us November 13th - 15th, 2015, as The Junior League of Tampa welcomes over 14,000 shoppers to this annual event at the Florida State Fairgrounds Expo Hall. The Junior League of Tampa Holiday Gift Market presented by Publix features over 150 specialty merchants from across the country as well as a selection from local shops in and around the Tampa Bay Area. 
Holiday Gift Market is an annual fundraiser where 100% of the net proceeds support the League's programs and community projects in the areas of child welfare, education and literacy in the Tampa Bay area. Please visit www.jltampa.org to learn more about the League's projects and community impact. 
This event is a perfect time to get all of your holiday shopping done! The Junior League of Tampa Holiday Gift Market merchants will be selling everything from gifts, holiday decor, women's and children's clothing, jewelry, food, art and much more! 
  
General Admission HGM Kickoff Party Hours:
 
Thursday, November 12, 2015, 7:00pm-10:00pm
 
HGM Kickoff Party includes exclusive sneak peak of our merchants, enjoy hors d'oeuvres, cash bar with wine and spirits, live entertainment, gift basket raffles, and shopping!  Please note that contributors to Annual Campaign may be entitled to General Admission HGM Kickoff Party Tickets.  Please visit www.JLTampa.org for more information on Annual Campaign and Donor Benefits.

Where can I park for this event?

It’s no secret that Houstonians love margaritas.  With over 300 restaurants and bars in the Houston area serving margaritas daily, Houston is arguably the margarita capital of the world!

Boasting an outdoor party, fueled by live Salsa, Top 40, Blues, and Motown bands, The Houston Margarita Festival is the ultimate margarita celebration.  Our elite, Houston-based band line-up sets the tone for innovative libations, salsa dancing, as well as limbo and other margarita competitions for cash prizes.  And, of course, it wouldn't be a Texan festival without great food vendors serving Mexican, Tex-Mex, Creole, seafood and other festival favorites, making us 3 for 3 to satisfy your appetite for meat, music and margaritas!  Listed as one of Houston's best festivals by the Houston Chronicle, we've served over 20,000 Margarita Lovers in the past, anticipating over 22,000 this year alone! Whether you're craving our signature Cucumber Apple, Hurricane, Coconut, Peach Mango, Raspberry, Pumpkin Spice, Green Apple or a classic Strawberry Margarita, we have over 22 fun flavors for you to enjoy while cruising the spacious lawn of Sam Houston Park with family and friends. Welcome to Margarita Heaven!

 

 

 

For ticket pricing and details visit: www.HoustonMargaritaFest.com

 

*Margarita flavors include, but are not limited to, Cucumber Apple, Bourbon St. Hurricane, Coconut, Peach Mango, Raspberry Passion, Pumpkin Spice, Green Apple, Strawberry Hill, Lots of Chocolate,  Jalapeno Pepper, Crazy In Love Watermelon, Grapefruit Groupie and Grrrrrrrape!

SCOPE MIAMI BEACH CELEBRATES 15th ANNIVERSARY EDITION  




  
SCOPE Art Show returns to the sands of Miami Beach for its 15th anniversary edition, amidst tremendous support from the City of Miami Beach, an unprecedented outpouring of critical acclaim from press, curators and collectors, and a digital and social media outreach campaign that garnered over 300 million impressions, including praise in The New York Times, Forbes, Artnet, Artinfo, The Huffington Post and The New York Post, amongst other publications.  
SCOPE Miami Beach’s monumental pavilion will once again be situated on historic Ocean Drive to welcome 45,000 visitors over the course of 6 days. Over 125 international Exhibitors will present groundbreaking emerging work, alongside SCOPE’s Breeder and Featured Programs.  
SCOPE Miami Beach opens to VIPs and Press on Tuesday December 1, for its Platinum First View and Preview events; the show will run December 2 - 6, 2015.  
With over 75 art fairs spanning more than 15 years, SCOPE is celebrated as the premier showcase for international emerging contemporary art and multi-disciplinary creative programming. Renowned for its uncanny ability to forecast new visual trends that are embraced globally, SCOPE Art Shows garner extensive critical acclaim and over 500 million annual impressions across print, digital and television. With cumulative sales well over one billion dollars and attendance of 1.2 million visitors, SCOPE Art Show is the largest and most global emerging art fair in the world.

Comics, Anime, Manga, Cosplay, Hollywood Stars, Dealer, Walking Acts, Exhibits, Audiobooks, Games, Fun, Parties - Comic Con is coming to Germany in June 2016. Infos: www.comiccon.de 
  
FAQs 
  
Was zahlen Kinder unter 6 Jahren? 
Kinder unter 6 Jahren haben freien Eintritt wenn Sie in Begleitung eines Erziehungsberechtigten kommen.  
  
Muss ich mich am Einlass ausweisen oder gibt es eine Altersbeschränkung für das Event? 
Es gibt keine Altersbeschränkung für die Comic Con Germany. Es gilt das deutsche Jugendschutzgesetz. 
  
Wie komme ich zum Event und wie sieht es mit Parkplätzen aus? 
Die Messe Stuttgart befindet sich direkt an der A8 in unmittelbarer Nähe vom Stuttgarter Flughafen. 
Angeschlossen an das Messegelände ist das Bosch Parkhaus für Besucher der Messe. Sollten alle Parkplätze auf dem Messe- und Kongressgelände belegt sein, werden die Besucher durch das Parkleitsystem zu den Parkplätzen am Fughafen umgeleitet. 
Vom Stuttgarter Hauptbahnhof aus fährt die S-Bahn direkt zur Messe. Die Messe verfügt außerdem über Anschlüsse an das Fernbusnetz. Weitere Infos auf unserer Webseite www.comiccon.de und unter www.messe-stuttgart.de/besucher/anreise-und-unterkunft/anfahrt/ 
  
Wie kann ich den Veranstalter kontaktieren, wenn ich Fragen habe? 
info@comiccon.de oder im Impressum von www.comiccon.de 
  
Ist meine Registrierung/mein Ticket übertragbar? 
Ja, Du kannst Dein Ticket auf andere Personen übertragen, falls Dir etwas dazwischenkommt. Du kannst Tagestickets auch einfach auf einen anderen Tag umbuchen. 
  
  
Schwerbehinderung und Begleitpersonen 
  
Schwerbehinderte Menschen mit dem Merkzeichen "B" im Ausweis dürfen eine Begleitperson kostenfrei auf die Veranstaltung mitnehmen. Schwerbehinderte Menschen erwerben bitte einfach das gewünschte Ticket, die Begleitperson benötigt kein Ticket sondern wird von uns am Einlass durchgelassen.  
  
Muss ich das ausgedruckte Ticket mitbringen? 
Du bringst entweder das ausgedruckte Ticket mit oder zeigst uns dein Ticket auf deinem Handy, so daß wir es einscannen können. 
  
Wie sehen die Rückerstattungsbedingungen aus? 
Rückerstattungen sind leider nicht möglich, siehe auch unsere AGBs auf www.comiccon.de 
  
Der Name auf der Registrierung/dem Ticket stimmt nicht mit dem Namen des Teilnehmers überein. Ist das ein Problem? 
Nein das ist kein Problem.

Whether you are a graduate, unemployed, new to Canada, a seasoned veteran looking to change careers, or even a student new to the workforce, Canada Job Expo is a great place to begin your career path. Canada Job Expo provides plenty of information, job resources and discussions and opportunities for employment. 
This expo is one of the most attended and free job fairs in the Greater Toronto Area with an environment of networking, learning and a day of professional interactions. 
  
Our past events have included major Canadian employers like  Apple Canada, Bell Canada, Canada Post, Desjardins, Moosehead Breweries, Toronto Police, Ontario Public Service (Ministry of Govt. Services) and a host of employers from Alberta, Manitoba, British Columbia as well as International Organizations.  
Please also join our mailing list on our home page to receive event updates.  
  
This expo brings Canadian employers, various organizations and educational institutions together with skilled workers and students for a day of networking, learning and employment advice. There are five free workshops available to everyone who attend this one day event. For further information, visit the website www.canadajobexpo.com 
  
This event is FREE to job seekers and those in between careers. Everyone is welcome to attend and gain something out of it. There are no restrictions on who can attend.  
  
For organizations looking to register a booth with us, please contact us for further details, cost, registration process etc. 
  
Please note we are also collecting donations to help the needy in Nepal. Any amount will help, donations however are not mandatory, just a suggestion. Thank you again.

description.text:
Tickets on sale Thursday, Aug. 6 @ 10am. Tickets are Non-Refundable. 
Enthusiast Member pre-sale on Tues. Aug. 4 (beginning at 12am) and Wed. Aug. 5 (ending at 11:59pm). Members will receive an email invitation to participate in the pre-sale. 
  
About the Event: Craft beer fans converge on Eastern Market for one of the largest all-Michigan beer tastings in the state. Tickets include 15 tasting tokens which can be exchanged for 3 oz. samples of over 500 beers locally crafted by more than 70 Michigan breweries. 
  
Guests will also enjoy on-stage entertainment from local musicians, and a selection of food from Detroit-area brewpubs and restaurants will be available for purchase. 
  
FAQs 
  
What is the refund policy? 
 Tickets are NON-REFUNDABLE. The festival will occur rain or shine. 
  
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event? 
All festival attendees must be 21 or older to enter, even if they are designated drivers and are not drinking. A valid government ID (driver's license, passport, etc.) is required for festival entry, with NO exceptions. 
  
Where do I pick up my tokens? 
You can pick up tokens from the token tent immediately after entering the festival. 
  
Why do I need to use tokens if I already paid for a ticket? 
The Michigan Brewers Guild utilizes drink tokens and specially marked cups to assure that we comply with Michigan Liquor Control Commission regulation and have a controlled means of serving beer. All festivals attendees are expected to willingly provide a token for each and every sample of beer received. Thank you for your cooperation which keeps us in compliance with state law. 
  
What are my transport/parking options getting to the event? 
There are several serface lots in the Eastern Market area as well as street parking. 
Designated Driver tickets will be available at the event (non-drinking ticket), so groups are encouraged to bring a DD. Alternative transportation can be arranged through companies such as Uber and Checker Cab. Some retailers run bus tours - check out Motor City Brew Tours (multiple pick-up locations) and One-Eyed Betty's (Ferndale). Shuttle transportation may also be available from area hotels. 
  
What can/can't I bring to the event? 
The following items are not permitted on festival grounds: outside alcohol, glass containers, children (with the exception of immobile infants - see FAQ below), animals, bicycles, skateboards, or rollerskates/rollerblades. 
  
You may bring any of the following items with you to the festival: water and other non-alcoholic beverages in non-glass containers, food, coolers, backpacks.  
  
Can I bring my baby to the festival? What about a stroller? 
Immobile infants are permitted inside the festival as long as they are in a baby backpack or carrier. Strollers are not recommended as the event will be crowded, and may be refused entry at the gate depending upon conditions. Children old enough to walk on their own are not permitted into the festival, for their own safety.  
  
Is my registration/ticket transferrable?  
Yes, tickets are transferrable, and you don't need to do anything special to transfer your ticket - you can simply give your ticket to another person and they'll have no trouble getting in. Each bar code will only scan one time.  
  
Can I sell my ticket to someone else?  
Yes, you are permitted to sell your ticket at face value plus whatever online Eventbrite service fee you paid. Michigan Brewers Guild does not permit scalping of tickets, which is illegal. We reserve the right to invalidate any tickets known to have been scalped.  
  
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event? 
You must bring a ticket with you to be scanned to allow you entry to the festival. This ticket can either be printed or can be the electronic version accessible on your smartphone or wireless device.  
  
Can I buy a Designated Driver ticket and then buy tokens for drinks if I change my mind? 
No. Servers will not pour beer to Designated Drivers, and anyone caught drinking on a Designated Driver ticket will be immediately ejected from the festival. If you want to drink any beer at the festival, you should plan on buying a full-price drinking ticket. 
  
Where can I find more information about the festival? 
For the most current information, visit our website at http://www.mibeer.com/summer-festival.
